article.headline: Denver 64, Arkansas State 57
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Dereke Tipler scored 18 points to lead Arkansas State to a 92-73 victory over Rhodes College in an exhibition game Monday. Tipler also had six rebounds and four assists. Kitus Witherspoon scored 15 points; Jerry Nichols and Isaac Wells each added 12 points, and Jim Jones scored 10. For Rhodes, Joe Thompson scored a game-high 24 points on 8-of-13 shooting, hitting several from 25 feet. And Arkansas State was down 52-40 at the half.
